news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra sale bookings rise 1% to Rs 254 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: The sale bookings rose 18 per cent to Rs 560 crore during April-September period of 2024-25 from Rs 476 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: China banks to lower interest rates on existing mortgages from October 25
news.para: Chinese policymakers have unveiled a string of stimulus measures in recent weeks aimed at boosting an economy blighted by a years-long property sector crisis and chronically low consumption.

news.title: Construction now must for industry land transfers: Arun Vir Singh, CEO, YEIDA
news.para: The directive issued by YEIDA CEO Arun Vir Singh states that ownership changes — whether due to alterations in the constitution, shareholding, or blood relations — will only be permitted if the allottee has obtained necessary map approvals and started construction on the plot.

news.title: Construction works threatening local ecosystem in Punjab: NGT issues notice
news.para: ​​ The green body was hearing a matter where it had taken suo motu (on its own) cognisance of a newspaper report regarding the Punjab forest department raising alarm over the activities.

news.title: Maharashtra government to regularise 27,000 illegal constructions in Ulhasnagar
news.para: Ahead of Lok Sabha elections early this year, the state had also reduced the penalty imposed for legalising constructions in the city. Despite this, revenue department officials were confused about the format in which the property card should be given to the owner after regularisation.

news.title: UPSIDA to launch e-auction for 43 plots across Uttar Pradesh
news.para: This upcoming e-auction will facilitate the auctioning of commercial plots in regions such as Bareilly, Jalaun, Barabanki, Prayagraj, Moradabad, and Trans Ganga City in Unnao.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL extends request for proposal date for two riverfront plots
news.para: The submission deadline was extended from Oct 15 to Oct 22, giving interested parties more time to prepare their bids.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to impose 9.15% interest on delayed property dues
news.para: Estate officer UP, Pawan Kumar Gangwar, said, "We will adjust the annual interest rate based on the SBI EBLR (External Benchmark Linked Rate) and issue recovery notices accordingly. Those who make payments on time will not be required to pay additional interest."

news.title: Unitech Group threatens to halt construction over buyers' unpaid dues
news.para: The notice comes at a time when construction work has resumed on a number of Unitech projects after almost a decade. The board said it was struggling to continue with the pace of construction in the absence of a steady flow of funds.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body revives plan for 47 plots in Indirapuram Extension
news.para: "The plan covers a total area of 30,000 sqm in this phase. The land will be divided into 47 residential and three commercial plots. The land parcels will be auctioned after they are developed," said a GDA official.

news.title: Mhada's Konkan board announces lottery for sale of 12,626 houses and 117 plots
news.para: The housing units are located in Thane city and district, Kalyan, Titwala, Palghar, Raigad, Ratnagiri, and Sindhudurg's Oras, Vengurla, and Malvan.

news.title: MHADA reduces additional area charges to 110% of ready reckoner rate in Mumbai
news.para: However, many beneficiaries are unable to afford this additional cost, which has delayed their permanent rehabilitation. Jaiswal noted that these payment challenges have caused a large backlog of unresolved cases with the Board, making it difficult to complete the rehabilitation process.

news.title: Mhada's Pune board launches registration process for sale of 6,294 houses
news.para: These housing units are across Pune, Pimpri-Chinchwad, Solapur, Kolhapur, and Sangli districts, including areas under the Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA).

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves housing plan for Bandra government Colony
news.para: A high-level committee under the chairmanship of chief secretary Sujata Saunik will take a decision regarding the location, number of govt employees and other procedures, said officials.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM launches 'Sampada-2' for e-registration of property documents
news.para: Speaking on the occasion, Yadav said that the Digital India Mission, initiated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, is now fulfilling the diverse needs of the common man like a "Kalpvriksh".

news.title: Kochi metro to begin construction of two more stations on phase II
news.para: A total of 0.235 hectares will be acquired for SEZ station while 0.1810 hectares will be acquired for Chittethukara station. Earlier, govt had granted permissive sanction to KMRL to begin construction work of Infopark station, and the work has already commenced.

news.title: DMRC seeks over Rs 6,200 crore for 2024-25 in revised budget from Delhi government
news.para: In a letter to the transport department of Delhi, DMRC has stated that it will need Rs 2,872 crore to pay its share of the loan taken from Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) to expand the metro network in the capital, and over Rs 2,000 crore for the exchange rate fluctuation, which needs to be released this year.

news.title: Goa government extends tenant verification drive by five days
news.para: The initiative, which began on Oct 1, was scheduled to conclude on Oct 10. Chief minister Pramod Sawant said that it is necessary to conduct tenant verification as, in some rape and murder cases, migrants are involved.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to raise Rs 6,000 crore
news.para: In August 2024, National Company Law Tribunal-Mumbai bench approved the resolution plan submitted by Oberoi Realty in relation to the corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) of Nirmal Lifestyle Realty (NLRPL).

news.title: Maharashtra RERA temporarily switches to old website due to issues with new platform
news.para: MahaRERA chairman Manoj Saunik conducted a review meeting after receiving numerous complaints about issues hampering user experience on MahaCRITI website. The problems were causing delays in availing services, which prompted immediate action from the authority, a MahaRERA official told TOI.
